uiGet(25.10)                                                      uiGet(25.10)

Name
       uiGet  -  Retrieves  the current value of the specified property of the
       element that is being queried

Syntax
       uiGet

       [-help]

       [<name>]

       [-quiet]

       [ -before | -checked | -children | -command

         | -disabled | -dockwin | -enablevar | -foreground

         | -geometry | -icon | -in | -label | -menu | -menuseparate

         | -message | -movable | -newline | -shortcut

         | -statusbar | -title | -toolbar | -tooltip

         | -type | -underline | -value | -variable

         | -visible | -visiblevar | -windowstatus ]

       Retrieves the current value of the specified property  of  the  element
       that  is  being queried. Using the uiGet command, you can query all the
       properties in the uiAdd command for each type. In  addition,  depending
       on the type, some special properties are supported too as described be-
       low:

              * For elements of type menu/submenu/toolbar:

                     * uiGet <name> -children

                       Returns  a list of all the child elements of the speci-
                       fied interface element.

              * For main (main window):

                     * uiGet main -menu

                       Returns a list of all the menus in the main window.

                     * uiGet main.layout -toolbar

                       Returns the list of all the toolbars in the  main  win-
                       dow.

                     * uiGet main -statusbar

                       Returns the status bar in the main window.

                     * uiGet main -geometry

                       Returns  the  geometry of the main window in the format
                       <width>x<height>+<x>+<y>.

                     * uiGet main -title

                       Returns the title of the main window.

                     * uiGet main -closecmd

                       Returns the close confirmation command of the main win-
                       dow.

                     * uiGet main -visible

                       Returns the visibility status of the main window.

              * For statusbar:

                     * uiGet name -message

                       Returns the current message of the status bar.

                     * uiGet name -visible

                       Returns the visibility status of the status bar.

                     * uiGet name -in

                       Returns the parent element of the status bar.

       The statusbar also supports the -enablevar and -visiblevar parameters.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each uiGet parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man uiGet

       <name> Specifies as a string the name of the interface element you want
              to query. If multiple widgets are found with  the  same  <name>,
              the  first  matched widget is queried. Returns an error if there
              is no element with the specified name.

       -before <name>
              When specified, returns the element that occurs before the  ele-
              ment identified by <name>.

       -checked
              Returns  the  on/off  state  of the specified check box or radio
              button. If the check box or radio button  is  selected,  returns
              true. If it is deselected, returns false.

       -children
              Returns child elements of specified interface element.

              Note:  You  can  use  this parameter with elements of type menu,
              submenu, and toolbar.

       -command
              Returns the Tcl command to be executed when the  specified  ele-
              ment you are adding is invoked.

              Note:  You  can use the -command parameter only with elements of
              type command, check, radio or toolbutton.

       -disabled
              When specified, returns whether the specified interface  element
              is enabled (false) or disabled (true).

              Note:  You can use the -disabled parameter only with elements of
              type menu, submenu, command, check, radio or toolbutton. The pa-
              rameter is NOT applicable for elements of type toolbar and sepa-
              rator.

       -dockwin
              Returns the dockwidget.

       -enablevar
              Represents the Tcl global variable for Enable status.

       -foreground
              Returns the foreground color of the icon for the specified tool-
              button.

              Note: You can use the -foreground parameter only  with  elements
              of type toolbutton.

       -geometry
              Returns the width, height, and coordinates of the main window.

              Note:  The  -geometry  parameter is applicable only for the main
              window, which is type main.

       -icon  Returns the file name of the specified toolbutton.

              Note: The -icon parameter is applicable  only  for  elements  of
              type toolbutton.

       -in    Returns the name of the parent element.

       -label Returns the label of the specified element.

              Note: This parameter is NOT applicable for elements of type sep-
              arator.

       -menu  Returns the names of the menus in the main window.

              Note:  This  parameter  is  applicable only for the main window,
              which is type main.

       -menuseparate
              Returns the tear-off status of the specified menu or submenu.

              Note: This parameter is applicable for elements of type menu and
              submenu.

       -message
              Returns the message on the status bar.

              Note: This parameter is applicable only for the status bar.

       -movable
              Returns whether or not the specified toolbar is movable.

              Note: The -movable parameter is applicable only for elements  of
              type toolbar.

       -newline
              Returns  whether  or  not  the specified toolbar starts in a new
              row.

              Note: The -newline parameter is applicable only for elements  of
              type toolbar.

       -quiet Displays  the  current  settings for the specified parameters in
              the Tcl list format.

       -shortcut
              Returns the shortcut key for a command, check box, radio button,
              or toolbutton.

              Note: You can use the -shortuct parameter only with elements  of
              type command, check, radio, or toolbutton.

       -statusbar
              Returns the name of the main window's status bar.

              Note:  This  parameter  is  applicable  only for the main window
              (main).

       -title Returns the text on the main window's title bar.

              Note: This parameter is applicable  only  for  the  main  window
              (main).

       -toolbar
              Returns the toolbars in the window.

       -tooltip
              Returns  the  tooltip text for the specified toolbar or toolbut-
              ton.

              Note: The -tooltip parameter is applicable only for elements  of
              type toolbar and toolbutton.

       -type  Returns the type of the specified element.

       -underline
              Returns the integer index of the underlined character in the el-
              ement label.

              Note: The -underline parameter is NOT applicable for elements of
              type toolbar, separator, and toolbutton.

       -value Returns the value stored in the associated variable of the spec-
              ified radio button.

              Note:  The  -value  parameter is applicable only for elements of
              type radio.

       -variable
              Returns the Tcl global variable for the specified check  box  or
              radio button.

       -visible
              Returns the visibility status of the element.

       -visiblevar
              Represents the Tcl global variable for Visible status

       -windowstatus
              Returns the widget window status. This option returns one of the
              following  values, depending on the window status, assuming that
              tool was launched in the GUI mode:

              * Minimized

              * Maximized

              * Normal

              For example, if the main window is in the default  window  mode,
              and you run the following command:

              uiGet main -windowstatus

              the software returns:

              Normal

              If  the  window  is in the background, you can use the following
              command to bring the window to the forefront:

              uiSet main -visible 1

Examples
              * The following command returns the label on element named  ver-
                ify:

                uiGet verify -label

                The software returns the following:

                Verify

              * The  following  command  returns the names of all the menus in
                the main window:

                uiGet main -menu

                The software returns the following:

                file view edit partition fplan power  place  eco  clock  route
                timing safety verify pvs tools windows flow help

              * The following command returns the names of all the toolbars in
                the main layout:

                uiGet main.layout -toolbar

                The software returns the following:

                tbFile  tbEdit  tbView tbTools tbReport tbToolBox we main.lay-
                out.selectbar

              *

                The following command returns whether the Select  bar  in  the
                main layout is movable:

                uiGet main.layout.selectbar -movable

              * The  following  command  returns the window status of the main
                window:

                uiGet main -windowstatus

                The software returns the following (assuming the window is  in
                the maximized mode at the time):

                Maximized

              * The  following command returns the tear-off status of the View
                menu:

                uiGet view -menuseparate

                The software returns the following:

                true

